oakcurric:unit-3145
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Past routines and past events: imperfect tense"@en ;
  curric:slug "past-routines-and-past-events-imperfect-tense" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn how to form the imperfect tense for past habitual
  events with -ar, -er, -ir verbs. Irregular imperfect forms for 'ser' 'era' and 'eras' are
  also taught. Pupils reinforce their knowledge of the imperfect tense by exploring the text
  'El Quijote'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils are already familiar with singular forms of 'estar' in the
  imperfect tense. Now, they are introduced to using the imperfect tense to talk about past
  habitual events. They learn singular forms of the imperfect tense for -ar, -er, and -ir verbs
  in addition to irregular verb 'ser'. Pupils strengthen their knowledge of the preterite by
  contrasting it with the imperfect. They also revisit modal verbs, the difference between
  'ser' and 'estar', prenominal adjectives, and 'cuando' as a relative pronoun. Pupils revisit
  key sounds r, rr, l, ll, and stress patterns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3145-8 ;
  curric:id "3145"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.080052Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3122
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Describing how people feel: 'tener' and 'dar' + noun"@en ;
  curric:slug "describing-how-people-feel-tener-and-dar-plus-noun" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils combine 'tener' and 'dar' with nouns to form idiomatic
  expressions to talk about how people feel. They learn new forms of 'dar' first person
  plural 'damos' and third person plural 'dan', and a new form of 'querer' first person
  plural 'queremos'. Pupils learn new stress rules."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils use their existing knowledge of singular and plural
  forms of 'tener' in the present tense to create idiomatic expressions describing how people
  feel using 'tener' with a noun. Pupils add two new forms of 'dar' to their repertoire and
  combine new and revisited forms of 'dar' with nouns to talk about how people feel. Pupils
  revisit subject pronouns and when they are used in Spanish. Pupils consolidate 'quiero' and
  'quiere' and add 'queremos'. Pupils further their understanding of stress by learning a new
  rule.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3122-7 ;
  curric:id "3122"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.102393Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-3123
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Places: -ar, -er, -ir verbs 1st and 3rd person"@en ;
  curric:slug "places-ar-er-ir-verbs-1st-and-3rd-person" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupils' verb knowledge. They recap first and third person
  plural -ar, -er, and -ir verbs, and learn 'van a' to express future meaning. Pupils use
  'ir de' with nouns to talk about activities, and combine 'para' with the infinitive to
  mean 'in order to'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils develop the ways in which they can use verbs. Pupils
  build on their existing knowledge of the present tense of 'ir' with 'a' to express the future
  by adding 'van a'. They also use 'ir de' with new and revisited nouns to talk about
  activities and combine 'para' with new and revisited infinitives. Pupils consolidate -ar,
  -er, and -ir verbs, subject pronouns nosotros/as and ellos/as, singular and plural nouns, and
  indefinite articles, and work on a challenging text 'Bolivia: Un país diverso'. Pupils
  revisit key sounds cu plus a vowel, ll, l, ce, ci.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3123-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3123-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3123-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3123-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3123-5 ;
  curric:id "3123"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.154520Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having .

oakcurric:unit-3121
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities in and out of school: -er and -ir verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-in-and-out-of-school-er-and-ir-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the first and second persons singular of the preterite for
  -er and -ir verbs, contrasted with their present tense counterparts. Pupils form yes/ no
  questions in the present and preterite tenses, and learn that some adjectives precede the
  noun."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know how to form the first and second persons of the
  preterite for -ar verbs. In this unit, they learn how to do the same for -er and -ir verbs.
  Pupils strengthen their knowledge of the first and second persons of -er and -ir verbs in the
  present tense by contrasting them with their preterite counterparts to describe events in the
  past and present. Pupils expand their knowledge of word order with prenominal adjectives.
  They revisit stress rules and learn that if the stress is on the ante-penultimate syllable
  there will always be an accent.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3121-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3121-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3121-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3121-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3121-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3121-6 ;
  curric:id "3121"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.162934Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-3124
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities past and present: -ar verbs, pronouns, adverbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-past-and-present-ar-verbs-pronouns-adverbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to the third person singular preterite of -ar, -er,
  and -ir verbs. Pupils contrast these forms with their present tense counterparts. Key
  sounds revisited are z, que, qui. Pupils contrast z with ce and ci."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit furthers pupils' knowledge of -ar, -er and -ir verbs in the
  preterite by adding the third person singular. Pupils embed their knowledge of the present
  tense, contrasting present tense forms of verbs with preterite forms. Pupils consolidate
  singular forms of the preterite in a variety of activities. They revisit asking questions
  using question words and rising intonation, and are reminded of the difference between 'del'
  and 'de la'. Pupils revisit key sounds z, que, qui. They contrast z with ce and ci and learn
  the differences in pronunciation in the Spanish-speaking world.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3124-9 ;
  curric:id "3124"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.227937Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners .

oakcurric:unit-3133
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Past and future trips to Spain and Spanish festivals: -ar verbs, 'hacer', 'ir'"@en ;
  curric:slug "past-and-future-trips-to-spain-and-spanish-festivals-ar-verbs-hacer-ir" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits -ar verbs in the context of the text 'La Tomatina'. Pupils
  revisit 'ir a' to express future meaning in the context of planning a trip, and singular
  forms of 'hacer' and 'ir' in the preterite in the context of a past trip."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils embed the third person singular and plural of -ar
  verbs in the present tense with the exploration of the text 'La Tomatina'. Pupils consolidate
  using present singular forms of 'ir a' with an infinitive to express future meaning, and
  single forms of 'ir' and 'hacer' in the preterite. Revisited vocabulary from Year 7, and
  several revisited SSCs provide further consolidation opportunities.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3133-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3133-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3133-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3133-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3133-5 ;
  curric:id "3133"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.476520Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-3118
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Contrasting past and present events: -AR verbs singular persons"@en ;
  curric:slug "contrasting-past-and-present-events-ar-verbs-singular-persons" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the preterite. Pupils form the preterite of the first and
  second persons singular of -ar verbs. They contrast this with the present tense of the
  first and second persons singular of -ar verbs. Pupils ask questions in the preterite, and
  form negative sentences using 'no'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to the preterite, and is the first time they
  have used the past tense. Pupils learn first and second persons singular of -ar verbs. Pupils
  will learn how to conjugate the preterite for other persons and other verb types in future
  units. Pupils embed their knowledge of the first and second persons of -ar verbs in the
  present by contrasting them with their preterite forms. They revisit question words and
  negative sentences with 'no' and apply them to the preterite. Pupils are introduced to
  syllable structure and strong vowels.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3118-7 ;
  curric:id "3118"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.486393Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3129
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Family and friends: possessive adjectives, comparatives"@en ;
  curric:slug "family-and-friends-possessive-adjectives-comparatives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn possessive adjectives 'su', 'sus', 'nuestra',
  'nuestro'. They learn comparatives 'más/menos … que' and irregular comparatives ‘mejor
  que’ and peor que’. Demonstratives 'este', 'esta', 'estos', 'estas' are introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on their knowledge of possessive adjectives
  'mi', 'mis','tu', and 'tus' by adding 'su', 'sus', 'nuestra', 'nuestro' to their repertoire.
  Pupils embed 'está/están' for states and 'es/son' for traits with number and gender agreement
  for adjectives in sentences using comparatives, which are new to this unit. Pupils learn
  demonstratives 'este', 'esta', 'estos', 'estas' and use these in sentences with comparatives.
  In phonics, spelling change to -qué and -gué in 1st person preterite is introduced, and
  pupils revisit strong and weak vowels.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3129-7 ;
  curric:id "3129"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.702980Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-3126
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Friendships and birthday celebrations: pronouns, 'gustar'-type verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "friendships-and-birthday-celebrations-pronouns-gustar-type-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces object-verb-subject word order with direct object pronouns
  'lo' and 'la' and indirect object pronouns 'me', 'te', 'le'. Pupils describe events,
  friendships and relationships. Key sounds revisited are n, ñ, b, v."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils learn object-verb-subject word order, direct object
  pronouns 'lo' and 'la', and indirect object pronouns 'me', 'te', 'le'. They anchor their
  existing knowledge of personal 'a' in these sentences. In the next unit, pupils will use the
  indirect object pronouns with gustar-type verbs. Pupils revisit key sounds n, ñ, b, v.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3126-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3126-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3126-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3126-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3126-5 ;
  curric:id "3126"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.733801Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3117
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Places and plans: 'ir' for present and future plans"@en ;
  curric:slug "places-and-plans-ir-for-present-and-future-plans" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces 'voy', 'vas', 'va', 'vamos'. These forms of 'ir' are combined
  with 'a' to mean to go to. Pupils learn that 'a' and 'el' combine to make 'al' and
  contrast this with 'a la'. Pupils learn they can use a present tense form of 'ir' with 'a'
  and an infinitive expresses the future."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils learn 'voy', 'vas', 'va', and 'vamos' from 'ir'
  meaning 'to go'. They learn they can combine these forms with 'a' and an infinitive to
  express the future. In other units, pupils will learn other forms of the verb 'ir', and other
  ways to express the future. Pupils learn that 'a' works in a similar way to 'de' and can be
  combined with 'el' to form 'al', which is contrasted with 'a la'. Pupils revisit key grammar
  and vocabulary, and expand their personal repertoire working with the poem 'La Playa' by Juan
  Guinea Díaz. Pupils revisit key sounds v, b, rr, r, silent h.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3117-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3117-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3117-3 ,
