oakcurric:unit-3137
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities and opinions: pronouns, gustar-type verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-and-opinions-pronouns-gustar-type-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces plural direct object pronouns 'los' and 'las' and plural
  indirect object pronoun 'les'. Pupils revisit 'gustar'-type verbs, personal 'a',
  object-first word order, and singular and plural present tense -ar verbs. In phonics
  pupils revisit stress patterns."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on their knowledge of direct and indirect
  object pronouns by adding 'los', 'las' and 'les' to their repertoire. They anchor these in
  their existing knowledge of object-first word order, personal 'a', and gustar-type verbs.
  Pupils expand their knowledge of gustar-type verbs by using them in the infinitive. Plural
  and singular forms of -ar verbs are consolidated.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3137-9 ;
  curric:id "3137"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.799274Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

oakcurric:unit-3136
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Everyday life: possessive adjectives, pronouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "everyday-life-possessive-adjectives-pronouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits possessive adjectives 'mi', 'mis', 'tu', tus' and contrasts
  them with reflexive pronouns 'me', 'te'. Reflexive pronoun 'se' is taught and contrasted
  with 'su' and 'sus'. Pupils revisit 'es', 'son', 'está', 'están', present tense -ar verbs,
  and adjective-noun number agreement."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils expand their knowledge of reflexive pronouns by
  adding 'se' to 'me' and 'te' which they already know. Pupils refresh their knowledge of
  reflexive pronouns, and contrast them with possessive adjectives to highlight the difference
  between the two. Traits are covered with 'ser' and location is covered with 'estar' to
  reinforce the irregular forms of, and difference in meaning between, these two key verbs.
  Stress patterns are reinforced in sounds of the language.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3136-8 ;
  curric:id "3136"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.974543Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being .

oakcurric:unit-3132
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What is happening now: present continuous, 'este' and 'esta'"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-is-happening-now-present-continuous-este-and-esta" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn how to form the present continuous of -ar, -er, and -ir
  verbs to talk about what is happening now. Demonstratives 'esta' and 'estas' and modal
  verb 'querer' are revisited. In phonics, pupils revisit ante-penultimate syllable stress."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils use their knowledge of 'estar' in the present tense,
  and combine it with a present participle to form the present continuous. Demonstratives
  'esta' and 'estas' with a noun are contrasted with 'estás' and 'está' with a gerund to
  preempt a common misconception. Pupils strengthen their knowledge of 'querer' as a modal verb
  in the first and third person plural. In phonics, pupils revisit ante-penultimate syllable
  stress.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3132-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3132-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3132-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3132-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3132-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3132-6 ;
  curric:id "3132"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.976804Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-3131
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Asking questions: -ar, -er, -ir verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "asking-questions-ar-er-ir-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits past and present regular -ar, -ir, -er verbs. Pupils listen to
  and ask questions using rising intonation, and are reminded that Spanish does not use do,
  did or does to ask questions. Pupils revisit penultimate syllable stress."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate their knowledge of preterite singular
  forms of regular -ar, -ir, and -er verbs and irregular forms of 'hacer' and 'ir'. Pupils will
  learn plural forms of the preterite in another unit. They also consolidate present tense
  singular and plural regular -ar, -ir, and -er verbs. They revisit listening to and asking
  questions in the past and present using rising intonation, and are reminded that Spanish does
  not use do, did or does to ask questions. The unit revisits penultimate syllable stress.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3131-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3131-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3131-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3131-4 ;
  curric:id "3131"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.037251Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3142
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Times of change: -er, -ir, -ar verbs 1st and 3rd person"@en ;
  curric:slug "times-of-change-er-ir-ar-verbs-1st-and-3rd-person" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn plural forms '-imos' and '-ieron' for -er and -ir verbs
  in the preterite, and contrast these with their singular counterparts and '-imos' and
  '-emos' in the present tense. Pupils revisit possessive adjectives 'nuestro/a' and learn
  their plural forms 'nuestros/as'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit revisits plural preterite forms of -ar verbs. Pupils are already
  familiar with singular forms of -er and -ir verbs in the preterite, and now add '-imos' and
  '-ieron' to their repertoire. They refresh singular forms by contasting them with the new
  plural preterite forms, and also contrast preterite '-imos' with present tense '-imos' and
  '-emos', as this is an area of linguistic difficulty. Pupils revisit possessive adjectives
  'mi', 'mis', 'tu', 'tus', 'su', 'sus' and expand 'nuestro/a' to include plural forms
  'nuestros/as'. New sounds je, ja, jo, ju are compared to ge, ga, go, gu.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3142-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3142-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3142-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3142-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3142-5 ;
  curric:id "3142"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.090623Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3120
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing what people do: -ER and -IR verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "comparing-what-people-do-er-and-ir-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn to form the first person plural form of -er and -ir
  verbs, and the third person plural 'hacen'. They learn English has two translations of the
  Spanish present tense - present simple and continuous. Spanish subject pronouns are
  introduced. Stressed syllables are introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit furthers pupils' knowledge of -er and -ir verbs by adding the
  first person plural. Pupils embed their knowledge of the first person singular by contrasting
  it with the first person plural. Present tense forms of the verbs 'hacer', 'deber' and
  'poder' are taught or revisited. Pupils revisit 'deber' and 'poder' as modal verbs. They are
  introduced to the concept that English has present simple and present continuous translations
  of the Spanish present tense. Pupils build on their knowledge of syllable structure and learn
  rules for stress on final and penultimate syllables.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3120-8 ;
  curric:id "3120"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.093111Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3149
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Plans for the holidays: 'ir' + a + infinitive"@en ;
  curric:slug "plans-for-the-holidays-ir-plus-a-plus-infinitive" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils revisit the first person plural in the present tense, and
  contrast it with the first person plural in the preterite. They also revisit the present
  tense with future meaning, and all persons of the verb 'ir' with 'a' and an infinitive to
  express future intention."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils strengthen the first person plural in the preterite
  and present tenses by using adverbs to distinguish which tense is meant. Pupils consolidate
  the present tense with future meaning, and refresh all persons of the verb 'ir' with 'a' and
  an infinitive to express future meaning. They strengthen 'para' with an infinitive to express
  'in order to', and contrast this with their knowledge of 'para' to mean 'for'. Pupils revisit
  a range of vocabulary and sound-symbol correspondences from KS3 to maintain their working
  memory.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3149-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3149-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3149-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3149-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3149-5 ;
  curric:id "3149"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.182779Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3147
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Friends: 'ser', 'estar' and demonstrative adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "friends-ser-estar-and-demonstrative-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces demonstrative adjectives 'ese', 'esa', 'esos', 'esas' and
  possessive adjectives 'mío/a', 'tuyo/a', 'suyo/a'. The unit revisits personal 'a',
  gustar-type verbs, word order, direct and indirect pronouns, prenominal adjectives, 'ser'
  and 'estar', and gender and number agreement."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The first half of this unit is focused on consolidating several
  grammatical structures that pupils have already learned. Pupils also recap a range of
  vocabulary from Years 7 and 8. This focus on revisiting ensures vocabulary and grammar
  remains in pupils' working memory and builds a solid foundation for further learning. The
  second half of the unit introduces demonstrative adjectives 'ese', 'esa', 'esos', 'esas', and
  reactivates existing knowledge by contrasting them with 'este' and 'esta'. Pupils learn
  possessive adjectives 'mío/a', 'tuyo/a', 'suyo/a', and contrast them with 'mi', 'tu', su'.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3147-9 ;
  curric:id "3147"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.217361Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3108
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Places: definite articles, plural adjective agreement"@en ;
  curric:slug "places-definite-articles-plural-adjective-agreement" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, 'son' is introduced and contrasted with 'es'. Pupils add -s to
  adjectives for the plural form. They learn singular definite articles 'el' and 'la' and
  that these reflect the gender of all nouns. Plural 'los' and 'las' are also introduced.
  Key sounds learnt are ga, go, gu, ge, gi and j."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit anchors pupils' prior knowledge of the third person of 'ser'
  'es', and then teaches the third person plural form 'son'. Pupils increase their knowledge of
  plurals by adding -s to adjectives. Building on their knowledge of determiners, pupils learn
  definite articles 'el', 'la', 'los' and 'las' and their relation to gender, and form short
  sentences using nouns, determiners and 'es' or 'son'. Hard g is added to a, o, u and soft g
  is added to e and i to build on prior phonics knowledge, and j is taught.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3108-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3108-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3108-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3108-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3108-5 ;
  curric:id "3108"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.235581Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
