    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3109
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Celebrations: 'querer' and 'dar'"@en ;
  curric:slug "celebrations-querer-and-dar" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the singular forms of 'dar' and 'querer' and combines them
  with nouns and indefinite articles, to mean giving and wanting in the context of festive
  seasons. Key sounds learnt are n and ñ."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils further add to their repertoire of verbs with the
  singular forms of 'dar' and 'querer'. Vocabulary relating to festivities and family enables
  pupils to talk about the festive season. In future units, pupils will learn to combine
  'querer' with another verb to mean 'want to'. New sounds n and ñ are taught.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3109-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3109-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3109-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3109-4 ;
  curric:id "3109"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.251332Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight .

oakcurric:unit-3135
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My holidays: -ar, -er, -ir verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-holidays-ar-er-ir-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits singular forms of the preterite of regular -ar, -er, and -ir
  verbs, subject pronouns 'yo', 'tú', 'él', 'ella', question words and forming negative
  statements. In phonics, pupils identify the number of syllables in cognates and revisit
  final syllable stress."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate singular forms of the preterite of
  regular -ar, -er, and -ir verbs in the context of talking about past holidays. They will
  learn the plural forms in another unit. A subset of vocabulary from Years 7 and 8 is
  revisited. This will be a regular feature in Year 9 to ensure pupils regularly practice all
  words they have already learned. Pupils reinforce their knowledge that cognates in Spanish
  are pronounced differently to English, and identify how many syllables each word contains to
  reinforce knowledge of Spanish stress patterns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3135-7 ;
  curric:id "3135"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.304514Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3113
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and places: 'estar' and 'ser'"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-places-estar-and-ser" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn plural forms 'estamos' and 'están' and 'somos'. They
  contrast 'estar' for state or mood with 'ser' for traits. Pupils combine plural verbs with
  adjective agreement. They learn that 'de' and 'el' combine to form 'del' and contrast this
  with 'de la'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils further their knowledge of 'ser' and 'estar' by
  adding in plural forms 'estamos' and 'están' and 'somos', and revisiting other forms of these
  verbs. They anchor their understanding of state and mood with 'estar' and traits with 'ser'
  to talk about what people are like today or in general. Adjective agreement is revisited in
  combination with these verbs. Pupils are already familiar with the preposition 'de' and now
  combine it with the definite article following positional adverbs to talk about where
  something is. Pupils revisit key sounds cu with a vowel and ce, ci.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3113-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3113-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3113-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3113-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3113-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3113-6 ;
  curric:id "3113"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.354183Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being .

oakcurric:unit-3115
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What people do: -ER and -IR verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-people-do-er-and-ir-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces -er and -ir verbs using a subset of the top 25 verbs. Pupils
  learn singular forms and the third person plural to talk about what people do. They ask
  yes/no questions with -er and -ir verbs using raised intonation. Key sounds revisited are
  ga, go, gu, ge, gi, j."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to -ir and -er verbs. They learn to conjugate
  forms that are the same for both verb types. In future units, pupils will learn to conjugate
  forms where -er and -ir verbs differ. Pupils embed forming yes/ no questions using rising
  intonation by applying their knowledge to -er and -ir verbs. Pupils revisit key sounds ga,
  go, gu, ge, gi, j.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3115-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3115-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3115-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3115-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3115-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3115-6 ;
  curric:id "3115"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.356660Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3116
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Describing people and possessions: 'mi' and 'tu'"@en ;
  curric:slug "describing-people-and-possessions-mi-and-tu" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn possessive adjectives 'mi', 'mis', 'tu' and 'tus'. They
  contrast the third person singular with the third person plural of various verbs, and ask
  questions using question words. Key sounds revisited are n and ñ."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to possessive adjectives 'mi' and 'tu' for
  singular objects and 'mis' and 'tus' for plural objects. In another unit, pupils will learn
  'su' and 'sus'. Pupils embed their knowledge of 'es' 'son', 'está' 'están', 'tiene' 'tienen',
  and third person singular and plural -ar/-er/-ir verbs in the context of describing people
  and possessions. Pupils revisit question words. They revisit key sounds n and ñ.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3116-8 ;
  curric:id "3116"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.424059Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
