    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-use-reference-resources ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3110
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What we have: 'tener' plural persons, plural adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-we-have-tener-plural-persons-plural-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils work with an authentic text. They learn two plural forms of
  'tener' - 'tenemos' and 'tienen', to talk about who people have in their families. Pupils
  learn that in Spanish, the adjective comes after the noun. Key sounds learnt are v, b, rr,
  r, silent h."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on their knowledge of 'tener' with two new
  plural forms, and increase their repertoire of family-related vocabulary to talk about
  people's families. Pupils strengthen their knowledge of adjectives and adjective agreement
  and combine this with noun-adjective word order. Pupils contextualise this new knowledge with
  a range of previously learned grammar and vocabulary such as 'hay', 'tiene', 'está' to talk
  about places. Sounds v and b are contrasted, as are rr and r. New sound silent h is taught.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3110-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3110-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3110-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3110-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3110-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3110-6 ;
  curric:id "3110"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.340324Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3111
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities: information questions"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-information-questions" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces four new question words, including cuánto(s), cuál(es),
  quién(es), which require number agreement. Singular forms of the verb 'hacer' are
  introduced, which then can be combined with question words. Key sounds revisited are a, o,
  ge, gi, j."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils add four new question words to their repertoire, and
  revisit 'qué', 'dónde', 'cómo', 'quién'. Pupils use their knowledge of number agreement to
  ask questions with cuánto(s), cuál(es), quién(es), and embed their knowledge of a range of
  verbs in the present tense. New and revisited vocabulary about activities provide topics for
  asking questions. Pupils revisit the sound-symbol correspondence cu with a vowel when using
  question words. Pupils strengthen their knowledge of key sounds a, o, ge, gi, j.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3111-8 ;
  curric:id "3111"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.342257Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-3107
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Life at school and home: negation with 'no', plural nouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "life-at-school-and-home-negation-with-no-plural-nouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces 'no' to negate verbs. Pupils add -es to form the plural of
  nouns which end in a consonant. They use plurals and numbers to talk about how many. The
  irregular form 'hay' is introduced, and is contrasted with 'tener'. Key sounds learnt are
  z, que, qui."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils embed their knowledge of -ar verbs and other verbs by
  combining them with 'no' to form the negative. In future units, pupils will learn more ways
  to form the negative. They practise forming the plural with -s, and learn a new way of
  forming the plural with -es for nouns that end in a consonant and therefore do not follow the
  typical -o or -a gender marking. Indefinite articles are revisited by combining them with
  'hay' to mean 'there is' or 'there are'. New sounds z, que, qui are taught.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3107-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3107-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3107-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3107-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3107-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3107-6 ;
  curric:id "3107"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.395388Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3143
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Important events: present and imperfect continuous"@en ;
  curric:slug "important-events-present-and-imperfect-continuous" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils combine imperfect forms of 'estar' with a present participle
  to talk about events in progress, and use the preterite for interruptions. 'Donde' and
  'cuando' are introduced as relative pronouns for subject relative clauses. Demonstratives
  'estos' and 'estas' are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils already know how to form the imperfect tense using singular forms
  of 'estar', and how to form the present participle. Now they learn to combine these elements
  to talk about events in progress in the past. They refresh their knowledge of the preterite,
  which they use to talk about interruptions. Pupils are already familiar with subject relative
  clauses using 'que', and now add 'donde' and 'cuando' to their repertoire. They also
  strengthen their knowledge of demonstrative pronouns 'estos' and 'estas'. Pupils revisit key
  sounds b, v, n, ñ.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3143-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3143-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3143-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3143-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3143-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3143-6 ;
  curric:id "3143"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.545365Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3130
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Weekend activities and holidays: 'hacer' and 'ir'"@en ;
  curric:slug "weekend-activities-and-holidays-hacer-and-ir" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces singular preterite forms for irregular verbs 'hacer' and
  'ir', and revisits their present tense singular forms. Pupils combine adverbs of location
  with 'del' and 'de la' and use forms of 'ir' with 'al' and 'a la'. Pupils revisit final
  syllable stress."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit furthers pupils' knowledge of verbs in the preterite by adding
  'hice', 'hiciste', 'hizo', 'fui', 'fuiste', 'fue'. Pupils contrast these verbs with their
  irregular present tense counterparts. Pupils revisit adverbs of location with 'del' and 'de
  la' and anchor this knowledge to form sentences using adverbs of location and 'hacer'. They
  revisit 'al' and 'a la' and expand their use by combining them with 'ir' in the preterite.
  Rules around final syllable stress are revisited.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3130-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3130-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3130-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3130-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3130-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3130-6 ;
  curric:id "3130"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.650418Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past .

oakcurric:unit-3139
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Weekends: 'ser', 'estar', 'ir' and 'hacer'"@en ;
  curric:slug "weekends-ser-estar-ir-and-hacer" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits 'ser' versus 'estar', regular and irregular comparative
  adjectives, adjective-noun number and gender agreement, forming the present continuous,
  reflexive pronouns, personal 'a', direct and indirect object pronouns, and gustar-type
  verbs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides pupils with the opportunity to consolidate what they
  have learned in previous units. Regular revisiting of key grammatical structures ensures they
  remain in pupils' working memory and build a solid foundation for pupils to learn new grammar
  in future units. Likewise, vocabulary from Years 7 and 8 is also consolidated in this unit.
  In phonics, pupils revisit forming hiato with strong vowels.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3139-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3139-2 ,
