oakcurric:unit-3140
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "School is out! 'Ir' and 'ir' + a + infinitive"@en ;
  curric:slug "school-is-out-ir-and-ir-plus-a-plus-infinitive" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on 'ir'. Pupils learn the present tense second person plural
  form 'vais'. They revisit preterite singular forms of 'ir' and contrast these with present
  tense singular forms. Pupils also revisit plural forms of 'ir a' with an infinitive to
  express future meaning."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils expand their knowledge of present tense forms of 'ir'
  by adding second person plural form 'vais'. They use this to form sentences using 'vais a'
  with an infinitive to express future meaning, and also consolidate other plural forms of 'ir'
  with 'a'. They revisit singular forms of 'ir' in the preterite, and contrast these with
  singular present tense forms to talk about where people go and went. Pupils refresh combining
  'ir' with 'al' and 'a la', and adverbs ending '-mente'. In phonics, pupils revisit use of
  accents, and revisit key sounds gue versus ge and gui versus gi.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3140-7 ;
  curric:id "3140"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.700749Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3112
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What we can and must do: -AR verbs 1st person plural, modals 'poder' 'deber'"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-we-can-and-must-do-ar-verbs-1st-person-plural-modals-poder-deber" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils are introduced to the first person plural of -ar verbs, which
  they contrast with the singular. Pupils learn singular forms of modal verbs 'deber' and
  'poder', modal verbs in negative statements, 'querer' with an infinitive. Key sounds
  revisited are e, i, u, ca, co, cu."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils anchor their knowledge of -ar verbs with more
  prototype verbs, and build on this by adding the first person plural. Pupils will already be
  familiar with singular 'querer' plus a noun, and now learn to combine this with the
  infinitive to mean 'want to'. They also learn singular forms of modal verbs 'deber' and
  'poder' and combine these with the infinitive. Pupils draw on their knowledge of negation to
  negate sentences with modal verbs. Pupils revisit key sounds e, i, u, ca, co, cu.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3112-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3112-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3112-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3112-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3112-5 ;
  curric:id "3112"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.749200Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3125
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Relationships and daily life: personal 'a', pronouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "relationships-and-daily-life-personal-a-pronouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn how to use personal 'a'. Pupils are introduced to
  reflexive verbs and reflexive pronouns 'me' and 'te'. They contrast these with possessive
  adjectives 'mi' and 'tu'. Key sounds revisited are hard g with ga, go, gu, and soft g with
  ge, gi, j."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' knowledge of verbs in the present tense and
  provides them with new ways to talk about people with personal 'a' and reflexive verbs and
  pronouns. Pupils strengthen their knowledge of possessive adjectives 'mi', 'mis', 'tu' and
  'tus', contrasting 'mi' and 'tu' with reflexive pronouns 'me' and 'te'. Pupils revisit key
  sounds hard g with ga, go, gu, and soft g with ge, gi, j.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3125-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3125-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3125-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3125-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3125-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3125-6 ;
  curric:id "3125"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.768080Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners .

oakcurric:unit-3144
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Important events: 'tener' present and preterite"@en ;
  curric:slug "important-events-tener-present-and-preterite" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces singular preterite forms of 'tener', and revisits its
  singular present tense forms. Singular forms of the imperfect tense of 'estar' are
  introduced, and present tense singular forms are revisited. Pupils learn relative pronoun
  'que' in subject relative clauses."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils add to their repertoire of verbs in the preterite
  with singular forms of 'tener' 'tuve', 'tuviste', 'tuvo'. Pupils strengthen their knowledge
  of 'tener' in the present tense and consolidate the use of 'tener que' plus an infinitive.
  Pupils refresh knowledge of singular present tense forms of 'estar', and are introduced to
  the imperfect tense with 'estaba', 'estabas', 'estaba' for both location and states. Pupils
  will learn more imperfect verbs in another unit. This unit introduces relative pronoun 'que'
  and subject relative clauses. Pupils revisit key sounds z, s, ce, ci.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3144-7 ;
  curric:id "3144"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.873632Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being .

oakcurric:unit-3146
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Work and school: 'ser', 'estar' and 'ir'"@en ;
  curric:slug "work-and-school-ser-estar-and-ir" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits the second person plural form of -ar verbs and introduces the
  second person plural forms of -er and -ir verbs, including modal verbs. Pupils learn the
  plural forms of possessive adjectives 'vuestros' 'vuestras'. Pupils revisit using the
  present simple to express a future meaning."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate the present tense second person plural
  form of -ar verbs, and contrast this with the second person singular. They also consolidate
  known irregular verbs 'eres' and 'sois', and 'vas' and 'vais'. Pupils build on this knowledge
  by learning the second person plural forms of -er and -ir verbs, including modal verbs
  'podéis', 'debéis', 'queréis' with an infinitive. Pupils are already familiar with singular
  possessive adjectives 'vuestro' and 'vuestra' and now learn plural forms 'vuestros' and
  'vuestras'. In phonics, pupils revisit stress patterns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3146-8 ;
  curric:id "3146"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.886135Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3128
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Visit to a Spanish city: -ar, -er, -ir verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "visit-to-a-spanish-city-ar-er-ir-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on singular present tense -ar, -er, and -ir verbs. The unit
  revisits infinitives and 'para' with an infinitive. Key sounds revisited are a, e, i, o,
  u, r, rr, co, ci, ll, que, qui, silent h, gu, go, gui, ge, z, b, v."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides pupils with the opportunity to consolidate what they
  have learned about -ar,-er, -ir verbs in the present tense. Pupils revisit singular forms of
  present tense verbs, infinitives, and 'para' with an infinitive. Revisited vocabulary from
  Year 7, and several revisited SSCs provide further consolidation opportunities. Pupils anchor
  this knowledge in the context of a visit to a Spanish city - Santa Cruz de Tenerife.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3128-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3128-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3128-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3128-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3128-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3128-6 ;
  curric:id "3128"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.889346Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

